🎯 1. Enumeration & Reconnaissance
The first step was to identify the services running on the target machine.

Nmap Scan: * Port 80: Apache Debian Default Page (HTTP).

Port 2222: SSH running on a non-standard port.

Directory Fuzzing: Using gobuster revealed a hidden directory: /simple.

Technology Identified: The site is running CMS Made Simple v2.2.8.

🕸️ 2. Web Exploitation (CVE-2019-9053)
Researching the CMS version led to CVE-2019-9053, a Time-based Blind SQL Injection.

The Challenge: The original exploit script (Python 2) required debugging to run on modern Python 3 environments.

The Fix: I modified the script to handle latin-1 encoding for the rockyou.txt wordlist and ensured the MD5 hashing used properly encoded byte strings.

Extraction: The script successfully extracted the database credentials.

Username: mitch

Password: secret     (🤣)

