👑 4. Privilege Escalation (The GTFOBins Path)
I checked for misconfigured sudo permissions using sudo -l. I discovered that Mitch could execute /usr/bin/vim as root without a password.

Vulnerability: This is a well-known GTFOBin. Many binaries, if allowed to run as sudo, can be "escaped" to spawn a shell.

Exploitation: By launching Vim with a specific flag, I forced it to execute a system shell before opening:

Bash
sudo vim -c ':!/bin/sh'
Result: Instant access to the root account. ⚡

